dicates player was signed as an injury-replacement player\n\n==Pre-season==\n===Bushfire Relief Match===\nIn January 2020, [[Netball Australia]] announced an All-Stars match for the pre-season featuring the [[Australia national netball team|Australian Diamonds]] and the best players from the Super Netball league. The match was played as a fundraiser for relief efforts for the [[2019\u201320 Australian bushfire season]], which had been particularly devastating.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://netball.com.au/news/diamonds-and-super-netball-unite-bushfire-relief|title=Diamonds and Super Netball unite for bushfire relief|date=14 January 2020|work=Netball Australia}}</ref> The teams were announced on 29 January 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://supernetball.com.au/news/netball-bushfire-relief-match-teams-unveiled|title=Netball Bushfire Relief Match Teams Unveiled|date=29 January 2020|work=Super Netball}}</ref>\n\n{{netballbox\n | bg         = #EEEEEE\n | date       = 1 March 2020\n | time       = 1:00 pm\n | report     = \n | stats      = \n | team1      = '''{{nb|Australia}}'''\n | score1     = \n | team2      = {{flagicon|UN}} '''All-Stars'''\n | score2     = \n | Q1         = \n | Q2         = \n | Q3         = \n | Q4         = \n | H1         = \n | H2         = \n | ET         = \n | goals1     = \n | otherstat1 = \n | goals2     = \n | otherstat2 = \n | venue      = [[Sydney Super Dome|Qudos Bank Arena]], [[Sydney]] \n | attendance = \n | umpires    = \n | res-umpire = \n | TV         = \n | series     = \n}}\n\n===Team Girls Cup===\nThe league\u2019s [[pre-season]] tournament, known as the '''Suncorp Team Girls Cup''', was set to return for the second time. The tournament would have taken place between 27 and 29 March at the refurbished [[Sydney Olympic Park Tennis Centre|Ken Rosewall Arena]].<ref name=PST>{{cite web|url=https://supernetball.com.au/news/suncorp-team-girls-cup-fixture-released|title=Suncorp Team Girls Cup Fixture Released|work=Super Netball|date=5 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe eight Super Netball teams are split into two groups of four and play each of their group opponents once, before playing an inter-group match to determine places from first to eighth. All matches were set to be live-streamed on the Netball Live App and [[Telstra|Telstra TV]], with the final and the third and fourth place match to be broadcast on the [[Nine Network]].<ref name=PST/>\n\nHowever, on Friday the 13th of March, 2020, the Suncorp Super Netball League announced that the event would be cancelled for 2020 as a result of the COVID-19 pandemic.\n\n====Pool A Fixtures====\n{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WDL\n|update=|start_date=27 March 2020\n|team1=NSW|team2=COL|team3=GIA|team4=QLD\n\n|result1=SF |result2=C |result3=C |result4=C\n\n|win_NSW= |draw_NSW= |loss_NSW= |gf_NSW= |ga_NSW= |status_NSW=\n|win_COL= |draw_COL= |loss_COL= |gf_COL= |ga_COL= |status_COL=\n|win_GIA= |draw_MEL= |loss_GIA= |gf_GIA= |ga_GIA= |status_GIA=\n|win_QLD= |draw_QLD= |loss_QLD= |gf_QLD= |ga_QLD= |status_QLD=\n\n|name_NSW=[[New South Wales Swifts]]\n|name_COL=[[Collingwood Magpies Netball|Collingwood Magpies]]\n|name_GIA=[[Giants Netball]]\n|name_QLD=[[Queensland Firebirds]]\n\n|source=[https://supernetball.com.au/sites/supernetball/files/2020-02/sn_006%20-%202020_TeamGirlsCup_Fixture_A4.pdf Fixture]\n|res_col_header=Q\n|col_SF=green1 |text_SF=Final\n|col_C=yellow1 |text_C=Classification matches\n\n|winpoints=4\n|drawpoints=2\n|losspoints=0\n}}\n\n{{netballbox\n| report     = \n| date       = {{dts|format=dmy|2020|3|27}}\n| time       = 17:00\n| stats      = \n| team1      = '''[[New South Wales Swifts]]'''\n| score      = \n| team2      = '''[[Queensland Firebirds]]'''\n| goals1     = \n| goals2     = \n| venue      = [[Sydney Olympic Park Tennis Centre|Ken Rosewall Arena]]\n| attendance = \n| umpires    = \n| res-ump    = \n|}}\n{{netballbox\n| report     = \n| date       = {{dts|format=dmy|2020|3|27}}\n| time       = 20:10\n| stats      = \n| team1      = '''[