MVP_link  = \n| seasonslist      =  \n| seasonslistnames = \n| prevseason_link  = 2019 Suncorp Super Netball season\n| prevseason_year  = 2019\n| nextseason_link  = 2021 Suncorp Super Netball season\n| nextseason_year  = 2021\n}}\n\nThe '''2020 [[Suncorp Super Netball]] season''' will be the fourth season of the premier [[Netball in Australia|netball]] league in [[Australia]]. The season will begin on 2 May and conclude on 30 August 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://supernetball.com.au/news/2020-suncorp-super-netball-fixture-revealed|title=2020 Suncorp Super Netball fixture released|work=Super Netball|date=14 November 2019}}</ref> The defending premiers are the [[New South Wales Swifts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/sep/15/swifts-thrash-lightning-in-super-netball-grand-final-|title=Swifts thrash Lightning in Super Netball grand final|work=The Guardian|date=15 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\n===Teams===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! Team\n! Captain/s <small>(subject to change)</small>\n! Coach \n! Home Courts\n! Ref.\n|-\n| [[File:ANZ Thunderbirds.svg|15px]] '''[[Adelaide Thunderbirds]]'''\n| [[Chelsea Pitman]] &<br>[[Layla Guscoth]]\n| Tania Obst\n| [[Priceline Stadium]]<br>[[Adelaide Entertainment Centre]]\n| \n|-\n| [[File:SSN Magpies.png|15px]] '''[[Collingwood Magpies Netball|Collingwood Magpies]]'''\n| [[Madison Browne]] &<br>[[Geva Mentor]]\n| Rob Wright\n| [[Melbourne Arena]]<br>[[State Netball and Hockey Centre]]<br>[[Silverdome (Launceston)|Silverdome]]\n| \n|-\n| [[File:SSN Giants.png|15px]] '''[[Giants Netball]]'''\n| [[Jo Harten]]\n| Julie Fitzgerald\n| [[Sydney Olympic Park Tennis Centre|Ken Rosewall Arena]]<br>[[AIS Arena]]\n| \n|-\n| [[File:ANZ Vixens.svg|15px]] '''[[Melbourne Vixens]]'''\n| [[Kate Moloney]]\n| [[Simone McKinnis]]\n| [[Melbourne Arena]]<br>[[Margaret Court Arena]]\n| \n|-\n| [[File:ANZ Swifts.svg|15px]] '''[[New South Wales Swifts]]'''\n| [[Maddy Proud]]\n| Briony Akle\n| [[Sydney Olympic Park Tennis Centre|Ken Rosewall Arena]]\n| \n|-   \n| [[File:ANZ Firebirds.svg|15px]] '''[[Queensland Firebirds]]''' \n| [[Gabi Simpson]]\n| Roselee Jenke   \n| [[Queensland State Netball Centre|Nissan Arena]]\n| \n|-\n| [[File:SSN Lightning.png|15px]] '''[[Sunshine Coast Lightning]]'''\n| [[Laura Langman]]\n| Kylee Byrne\n| [[University of the Sunshine Coast#Netball stadium|University of Sunshine Coast Stadium]]\n| \n|-\n| [[File:ANZ Fever.svg|15px]] '''[[West Coast Fever]]'''\n| [[Courtney Bruce]]\n| [[Stacey Marinkovich]]\n| [[RAC Arena (Perth)|RAC Arena]]\n| \n|}\n\n===Format===\nThe season is played over fourteen rounds, allowing every team to play each other twice, once at home and once away. The top four teams on the [[Standings|ladder]] at the conclusion of the [[Season (sports)#Regular season|regular season]] qualify for the [[Playoffs|finals series]]. In the first week of the finals series, the 1st ranked team hosts the 2nd ranked team in the major semi-final (with the winner of that match to qualify for the [[Grand Final]]) and the 3rd ranked team hosts the 4th ranked team in the minor semi-final (with the loser of that match eliminated). The loser of the major semi-final then hosts the winner of the minor semi-final in the preliminary final. The winner of the major semi-final then hosts the winner of the preliminary final in the Grand Final.\n\n===Rule changes===\nThe Super Netball commission announced changes to the league structure in February. Rolling [[Substitution (sport)|substitutions]] during play will be permitted, as well as during stoppages and intervals, with no limit to the number of substitutions that can be made, and multiple substitutions allowed to be made at any one time. The substitute must tag hands with the player leaving the court before entering the field of play. Extra time in the event of draws will be introduced, after six matches were tied throughout the [[2019 Suncorp Super Netball season|previous season]]. The match will enter one 5-minute period of extra time. If at the end of this period teams remain tied, the match will be declared a draw. If a team has a one-goal or greater advantage at the end of the period, they will be declared the winner. The bonus point system in place for the past two seasons will remain, though no bonus points will be awarded for goals scored in extra time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://supernetball.com.au/news/suncorp-super-netball-rule-changes|title=Suncorp Super Netball Rule Changes|work=Super Netball|date=7 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bendigoadvertiser.com.au/story/6619737/harten-backs-extra-time-in-super-netball/?cs=2512|title=Harten backs extra time in Super Netball|date=6 February 2020|work=Bendigo Advertiser}}</ref>\n\n==Player transfers==\nThe league unveiled the list of non-contracted athletes on 14 August 2019, two weeks before that season's finals series were scheduled to commence.<ref name=firstlist>{{cite web|url=https://supernetball.com.au/news/suncorp-super-netball-releases-list-uncontracted-players|work=Super Netball|date=14 August 2019|title=Suncorp Super Netball Releases List Of Uncontracted Players|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815081204/https://supernetball.com.au/news/suncorp-super-netball-releases-list-uncontracted-players|archivedate=15 August 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> Teams had the exclusive right to re-sign any of their existing contracted players, their permanent/temporary replacement players or training partners, on single year or multi-year contracts for the 2020 and 2021 seasons. Contracts with players from other teams and leagues could not be announced until the signing period commenced on 16 September 2019. This period closed on 14 October 2019, upon which teams were required to have submitted their 10 senior-listed players for the 2020 season. Training partners could be signed by clubs at any time.<ref name=firstlist/>\n\n===Signings===\nThe following table is a list of players who moved clubs/leagues into Super Netball, or were elevated into a permanent position in the senior team, during the off-season. It does not include players who were re-signed by their original Super Netball clubs.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:78%; text-align:center; text-align:left;\"\n|+\n!Name\n!Moving from\n!Moving to\n!Ref\n|-\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Maddie Hay]]\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Giants Netball]] ([[Australian Netball League|ANL]]; training partner)\n|[[File:SSN Giants.png|15px]] [[Giants Netball]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.giantsnetball.com.au/maddie-hay-signs-for-2020/|title=Maddy Hay signs for 2020|date=6 September 2019|work=Giants Netball}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Molly Jovic]]\u2020\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Collingwood Magpies#Tasmanian Magpies|Tasmanian Magpies]] ([[Australian Netball League|ANL]])\n|[[File:SSN Magpies.png|15px]] [[Collingwood Magpies Netball|Collingwood Magpies]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=https://magpiesnetball.com.au/news/collingwood-magpies-ssn/two-more-for-browne|title=Two more for Browne and Jovic gets the call-up|date=12 September 2019|work=Collingwood Magpies Netball}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Melissa Bragg]]\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Collingwood Magpies#Tasmanian Magpies|Tasmanian Magpies]] ([[Australian Netball League|ANL]]; training partner)\n|[[File:SSN Magpies.png|15px]] [[Collingwood Magpies Netball|Collingwood Magpies]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=https://supernetball.com.au/news/bragg-earns-full-time-magpies-spot-2020|title=Bragg Earns Full-time Magpies Spot For 2020|work=Super Netball|date=24 September 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|RSA}} [[Ine-Mari Venter]]\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Melbourne Vixens]]\n|[[File:ANZ Firebirds.svg|15px]] [[Queensland Firebirds]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref name=Firebirds10>{{cite web|url=https://supernetball.com.au/news/firebirds-2020-playing-roster|title=Firebirds Release 2020 Playing Roster|work=Super Netball|date=30 September 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Rudi Ellis]]\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Melbourne Vixens#Victorian Fury|Victorian Fury]] ([[Australian Netball League|ANL]])\n|[[File:ANZ Firebirds.svg|15px]] [[Queensland Firebirds]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref name=Firebirds10/>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Macy Gardner]]\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Queensland Firebirds#Queensland Fusion|Queensland Fusion]] ([[Australian Netball League|ANL]]; training partner)\n|[[File:ANZ Firebirds.svg|15px]] [[Queensland Firebirds]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref name=Firebirds10/>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|JAM}} [[Jodi-Ann Ward]]\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Severn Stars]]\n|[[File:SSN Magpies.png|15px]] [[Collingwood Magpies Netball|Collingwood Magpies]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=https://magpiesnetball.com.au/news/collingwood-magpies-latest-netball-club-news/ward-a-magpie|title=Ward a Magpie|date=2 October 2019|work=Collingwood Magpies Netball}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Kate Eddy]]\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[New South Wales Swifts]]\n|[[File:ANZ Vixens.svg|15px]] [[Melbourne Vixens]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=https://melbournevixens.com.au/news/player-news/vixens-lock-in-kate-eddy-for-2020|title=Vixens lock in Kate Eddy for 2020|date=4 October 2019|work=Melbourne Vixens}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Lara Dunkley]]\u2020\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Melbourne Vixens]]\n|[[File:ANZ Firebirds.svg|15px]] [[Queensland Firebirds]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=https://supernetball.com.au/news/lara-dunkley-firebird-now|title=Lara Dunkley A Firebird Now|date=14 October 2019|work=Super Netball}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|NZ}} [[Kayla Cullen|Kayla Johnson]]\n|{{flagicon|NZ}} [[Northern Stars]]\n|[[File:ANZ Swifts.svg|15px]] [[New South Wales Swifts]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=https://supernetball.com.au/news/silver-fern-kayla-cullen-commits-swifts-2020-season|title=Silver Fern Kayla Cullen Commits to Swifts for 2020 Season|date=14 October 2019|work=Super Netball}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Maisie Nankivell]]\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Adelaide Thunderbirds#Southern Force|Southern Force]] ([[Australian Netball League|ANL]])\n|[[File:ANZ Thunderbirds.svg|15px]] [[Adelaide Thunderbirds]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref name=finaltransfer>{{cite web|url=https://supernetball.com.au/news/lenize-potgieter-signing-headlines-thunderbirds-2020-team-list|title=Lenize Potgieter Signing Headlines Thunderbirds 2020 Team List|date=15 October 2019|work=Super Netball}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|RSA}} [[Lenize Potgieter]]\n|{{flagicon|NZ}} [[Southern Steel]]\n|[[File:ANZ Thunderbirds.svg|15px]] [[Adelaide Thunderbirds]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref name=finaltransfer/>\n|}\n\u2020 Indicates player was signed as an injury-replacement player\n\n==Pre-season==\n===Bushfire Relief Match===\nIn January 2020, [[Netball Australia]] announced an All-Stars match for the pre-season featuring the [[Australia national netball team|Australian Diamonds]] and the best players from the Super Netball league. The match was played as a fundraiser for relief efforts for the [[2019\u201320 Australian bushfire season]], which had been particularly devastating.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://netball.com.au/news/diamonds-and-super-netball-unite-bushfire-relief|title=Diamonds and Super Netball unite for bushfire relief|date=14 January 2020|work=Netball Australia}}</ref> The teams were announced on 29 January 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://supernetball.com.au/news/netball-bushfire-relief-match-teams-unveiled|title=Netball Bushfire Relief Match Teams Unveiled|date=29 January 2020|work=Super Netball}}</ref>\n\n{{netballbox\n | bg         = #EEEEEE\n | date       = 1 March 2020\n | time       = 1:00 pm\n | report     = \n | stats      = \n | team1      = '''{{nb|Australia}}'''\n | score1     = \n | team2      = {{flagicon|UN}} '''All-Stars'''\n | score2     = \n | Q1         = \n | Q2         = \n | Q3         = \n | Q4         = \n | H1         = \n | H2         = \n | ET         = \n | goals1     = \n | otherstat1 = \n | goals2     = \n | otherstat2 = \n | venue      = [[Sydney Super Dome|Qudos Bank Arena]], [[Sydney]] \n | attendance = \n | umpires    = \n | res-umpire = \n | TV         = \n | series     = \n}}\n\n===Team Girls Cup===\nThe league\u2019s [[pre-season]] tournament, known as the '''Suncorp Team Girls Cup''', was set to return for the second time. The tournament would have taken place between 27 and 29 March at the refurbished [[Sydney Olympic Park Tennis Centre|Ken Rosewall Arena]].<ref name=PST>{{cite web|url=https://supernetball.com.au/news/suncorp-team-girls-cup-fixture-released|title=Suncorp Team Girls Cup Fixture Released|work=Super Netball|date=5 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe eight Super Netball teams are split into two groups of four and play each of their group opponents once, before playing an inter-group match to determine places from first to eighth. All matches were set to be live-streamed on the Netball Live App and [[Telstra|Telstra TV]], with the final and the third and fourth place match to be broadcast on the [[Nine Network]].<ref name=PST/>\n\nHowever, on Friday the 13th of March, 2020, the Suncorp Super Netball League announced that the event would be cancelled for 2020 as a result of the COVID-19 pandemic.\n\n====Pool A Fixtures====\n{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WDL\n|update=|start_date=27 March 2020\n|team1=NSW|team2=COL|team3=GIA|team4=QLD\n\n|result1=SF |result2=C |result3=C |result4=C\n\n|win_NSW= |draw_NSW= |loss_NSW= |gf_NSW= |ga_NSW= |status_NSW=\n|win_COL= |draw_COL= |loss_COL= |gf_COL= |ga_COL= |status_COL=\n|win_GIA= |draw_MEL= |loss_GIA= |gf_GIA= |ga_GIA= |status_GIA=\n|win_QLD= |draw_QLD= |loss_QLD= |gf_QLD= |ga_QLD= |status_QLD=\n\n|name_NSW=[[New South Wales Swifts]]\n|name_COL=[[Collingwood Magpies Netball|Collingwood Magpies]]\n|name_GIA=[[